ABAKALIKI – The Speaker of Ebonyi State House of Assembly, Francis Nwifuru, on Tuesday declared vacant the seats of more three Peoples Democratic Party’s (PDP) lawmakers. The affected lawmakers are Victor Aleke, Mrs. Franca Okpo and Okechukwu Ali. The Tuesday’s plenary was attended by only APC lawmakers. This is coming barely one week after a Federal High Court presided over by Justice Inyang Ekwo declared vacant, Speaker Nwifuru’s seat and those of 15 other APC lawmakers for defecting to the All Progressives Congress (APC) from the PDP. The speaker and the 14 APC lawmakers had before the court judgment that sacked them, declared vacant, the seats of the deputy speaker of the House, Odefa Obasi Ofeda, and two other lawmakers of the PDP, namely, Oliver Osi and Ngozi Eziulo. The trio had since approached the court which reversed the decision of the House. The speaker and the 14 APC lawmakers had last week, while reacting to the court judgment which sacked them, said they were dissatisfied with the judgment and had filed an appeal and stay of execution. But as at the time of filing this report, it was not certain if the speaker and the 14 APC lawmakers had got the stay of execution of the judgment that sacked them.